<inglise> REGULATION (EEC) No 2481/75 OF THE COUNCIL of 29 September 1975 amending Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 laying down special measures for improving the production and marketing of Community citrus fruits </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2481/75, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69, millega s&auml;testatakse erimeetmed &uuml;henduse tsitrusviljade kasvatamise ja turustamise parandamiseks 29. september 1975 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut; </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament (1); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (1) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 (2) of 9 December 1969 laying down special measures for improving the production and marketing of Community citrus fruits, as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 175/73 (3), provides for the granting of additional aid to small farmers to compensate for part of the loss of income caused by replanting; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 9. detsembri 1969. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69, millega s&auml;testatakse erimeetmed &uuml;henduse tsitrusviljade kasvatamise ja turustamise parandamiseks, (2) muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 175/73, (3) n&auml;hakse ette t&auml;iendava abi andmine v&auml;iketalunikele taasistutamise t&otilde;ttu saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu h&uuml;vitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas one of the conditions for the granting of this aid is that the area of the undertaking does not exceed five hectares; whereas, when the total area of the undertaking exceeds five hectares but the area fit for agricultural use does not exceed that limit since the rest of the land is not cultivable, the farmer's economic situation is the same as in the cases mentioned in the Regulation; whereas all farmers of an area fit for agricultural use not exceeding five hectares should receive identical treatment; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud abi andmise &uuml;ks tingimus on, et ettev&otilde;tte pindala ei &uuml;leta 5 hektarit; kui ettev&otilde;tte pindala on suurem kui 5 hektarit, kuid p&otilde;llumajanduslik maa seda piirm&auml;&auml;ra ei &uuml;leta, kuna &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud maa ei ole haritav, on taluniku majanduslik olukord sama, mis k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses nimetatud juhtudel; k&otilde;iki talunikke, kelle p&otilde;llumajanduslik maa ei &uuml;leta 5 hektarit, tuleks kohelda v&otilde;rdselt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 set up in particular a scheme of financial compensation to promote sales of Community-produced oranges and mandarins on Community import markets by means of contracts ensuring regular supplies for these markets; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 kehtestatakse rahalise h&uuml;vitamise kava, et edendada &uuml;henduses toodetud apelsinide ja mandariinide m&uuml;&uuml;ki &uuml;henduse imporditurgudel selliste lepingute abil, mis tagavad regulaarsed tarned nendele turgudele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas experience has shown that the contractual scheme referred to above has not had the desired results as regards the growth of Community outlets for the products in question; whereas, moreover, the increase in competition from certain producer third countries can only make it more difficult to market Community-produced citrus fruit on the Community market; </inglise>
<eesti> kogemus on n&auml;idanud, et eespool nimetatud lepingute s&uuml;steem ei ole andnud soovitud tulemusi k&otilde;nealuste &uuml;henduse toodete turustusv&otilde;imaluste parandamisel; lisaks sellele v&otilde;ib teatavatest kolmandatest tootjaliikmesriikidest l&auml;htuv suurem konkurents raskendada &uuml;henduses toodetud tsitrusviljade turustamist &uuml;henduse turul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas to counter these difficulties Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 should be modified by discontinuing the contractual scheme and increasing the amounts of financial compensation; whereas this compensation should be extended to include clementines; </inglise>
<eesti> nende raskustega v&otilde;itlemiseks tuleks muuta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69, kaotades lepingute s&uuml;steemi ja suurendades h&uuml;vitise summasid; seda h&uuml;vitist tuleks laiendada ka klementiinidele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas during the recent marketing years there have also been problems as regards the distribution of Community lemon production on the Community import markets; whereas, therefore, it is advisable, as a precautionary measure, to grant financial compensation in respect of this product for the remainder of the 1975/76 marketing year; </inglise>
<eesti> viimastel turustusaastatel on esinenud probleeme &uuml;henduse sidrunitoodangu jaotamisega &uuml;henduse imporditurgudel; seet&otilde;ttu on ettevaatusabin&otilde;una soovitatav anda k&otilde;nealuse toote puhul rahalist h&uuml;vitist &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud 1975/76. turustusaastaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to ensure the effectiveness of such a system, provision should be made for bringing up to date the amounts fixed in respect of oranges, mandarins and clementines, taking into account the trend of the basic and buying-in prices for the products concerned, </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse korra t&otilde;hususe tagamiseks tuleks s&auml;testada apelsinide, mandariinide ja klementiinide jaoks kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud summade ajakohastamine, arvestades asjaomaste toodete baas- ja kokkuostuhindade suundumusi, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The first indent of Article 4 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse 2511/69/EM&Uuml; artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 1 esimene taane asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "- the area of their undertaking which is fit for agricultural use does not exceed five hectares, " </inglise>
<eesti> "- nende ettev&otilde;tete p&otilde;llumajandusliku maa pindala ei &uuml;leta 5 hektarit," </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The text of Article 6 of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 shall be replaced by the following: (1) Opinion delivered on September 1975 (not yet published in the Official Journal). </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 artikli 6 tekst asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> (2) OJ No L 318, 18.12.1969, p. 1. (3) OJ No L 25, 30.1.1973, p. 2. "Sellers in the producer Member States shall receive, in accordance with the conditions set out below, financial compensation in respect of Community oranges, mandarins, clementines and lemons marketed in the other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> "Tootjaliikmesriikide m&uuml;&uuml;jad saavad allpool s&auml;testatud tingimustel rahalist h&uuml;vitist teistes liikmesriikides turustatud apelsinide, mandariinide, klementiinde ja sidrunite eest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, as regards lemons, this financial compensation shall only be granted for the 1975/76 marketing year. " </inglise>
<eesti> Sidrunite puhul antakse k&otilde;nealust rahalist h&uuml;vitist siiski &uuml;ksnes 1975/76. turustusaastal." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The text of Article 7 of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 artikli 7 tekst asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "1. For the 1975/76 marketing year the financial compensation shall be fixed as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> "1. 1975/76. turustusaastaks kinnitatakse rahaline h&uuml;vitis j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - 7.8 u.a./100 kg net for oranges of the Moro, Tarocco, Ovale calabrese, Belladonna, Navel and Valencia late varieties, </inglise>
<eesti> - 7,8 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta Moro, Tarocco, Ovale calabrese, Belladonna, Navel ja Valencia hiliste sortide puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - 6.7 u.a./100 kg net for oranges of the Sanguinello variety, </inglise>
<eesti> - 6,7 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta Sanguinello sordist apelsinide puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - 4.4 u.a./100 kg net for oranges of the Sanguigno and Biondo comune varieties, </inglise>
<eesti> - 4,4 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta Sanguigno ja Biondo comune sordist apelsinide puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - 6.7 u.a./100 kg net for mandarins, </inglise>
<eesti> - 6,7 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta mandariinide puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - 3.9 u.a./100 kg net for clementines, </inglise>
<eesti> - 3,9 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta klementiinide puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - 4.7 u.a./100 kg net for lemons. </inglise>
<eesti> - 4,7 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kg netomassi kohta sidrunite puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In subsequent marketing years the amount of financial compensation for oranges, mandarins and clementines shall be fixed each year before 1 August for the marketing year beginning during the following year according to the procedure laid down in Article 43 (2) of the Treaty, taking into account both the previous levels of this amount and the trend of the basic and buying-in prices of the products concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;rgnevateks turustusaastateks kinnitatakse apelsinide, mandariinide ja klementiinide rahaliste h&uuml;vitiste summad igal aastal enne 1. augustit j&auml;rgmise aasta jooksul algava turustusaasta kohta vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 43 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud korrale, v&otilde;ttes arvesse selle summa eelmiseid tasemeid ning asjaomaste toodete baas- ja kokkuostuhindade suundumusi. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the percentage of the variation of the financial compensation by comparison with the preceding marketing year may not exceed the percentage of the variation of the basic and buying-in prices. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahalise h&uuml;vitise varieerumise protsent ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada, v&otilde;rreldes eelmise turustusaastaga, baas- ja kokkuostuhindade varieerumise protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Financial compensation shall only be granted in respect of products belonging to quality classes Extra and I. " </inglise>
<eesti> Rahalist h&uuml;vitist antakse ainult ekstraklassi ja I klassi kuuluvate toodete puhul." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The text of Article 8 of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 artikli 8 tekst asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "1. </inglise>
<eesti> "1. </eesti>
<inglise> The financial compensation shall be paid to the sellers at their request, as soon as evidence has been furnished that the goods in question have entered the territory of the importing Member State and have been made available to the purchaser. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahalist h&uuml;vitist makstakse m&uuml;&uuml;jatele nende taotlusel, niipea kui on t&otilde;endatud, et k&otilde;nealune kaup on sisenenud importiva liikmesriigi territooriumile ning tehtud ostjale k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for applying this Article shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 33 of Regulation (EEC) No 1035/72. " </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikli &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1035/72 artiklis 33 s&auml;testatud korras." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The text of Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 2511/69 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2511/69 artikli 9 tekst asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "The rules governing the financing of the common agricultural policy shall apply to the financial compensation referred to in Article 6. " </inglise>
<eesti> "&Uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist reguleerivaid eeskirju kohaldatakse artiklis 6 nimetatud rahalise h&uuml;vitamise suhtes." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 October 1975. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. oktoobril 1975. Artikleid 2, 3 ja 4 kohaldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> Articles 2, 3 and 4 shall apply: - in respect of oranges, mandarins and clementines, from the beginning of the 1975/76 marketing year, </inglise>
<eesti> - apelsinide, mandariinide ja klementiinide puhul alates 1975/76. turustusaasta algusest, - sidrunite puhul alates k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise> - in respect of lemons, from the date of the entry into force of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
